Executive Profile
I. Martin Inglis  Chief Financial Officer and Executive Vice President, Battelle Memorial Institute, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 5 Board Members in 5 different organizations across 4 different industries.See Board Relationships66--
Background

		Mr. I. Martin Inglis serves as an Chief Financial Officer and Executive Vice President of Battelle Energy Alliance, LLC. Mr. Inglis joined Battelle in October 2004. Mr. Inglis worked for 32 years at Ford Motor Company most recently as the Group Vice President of Business Strategy. He played a key role in Ford's global governance and strategy and in championing diversity and talent development processes. During his tenure at Ford, Mr. Inglis held several key positions ... as the Chief Financial Officer, Group Vice President, Head of Ford North American and Corporate Vice President, President of Ford South American and Corporate Vice President and Head of Global Product and Business Strategy and Corporate Vice President. He served posts in Ford Lio Ho-Taiwan and Ford Europe-Essex, England. He serves as a Director at Brookhaven Science Associates, LLC and UT-Battelle, LLC. He has been an Independent Director at Carpenter Technology Corp. since 2007 and also serves as its Independent Lead Director. Mr. Inglis is a Member of The Conference Board Council of Chief Financial Officers. He is also on the Advisory Board of Fletcher Spaght Ventures, LP and Member of Fund Advisory Board at Reservoir Venture Partners. Mr. Inglis earned a B.A. degree in Business Economics, with honors, from Strathclyde University in Glasgow, Scotland.Read Full Background




