I. Martin Inglis

Age : 66Public asset : 134,748 USDLinked companies :  Carpenter Technology Corporation 





Summary 



Mr. Inglis is Executive Vice President and CFO of Battelle, a global science and technology enterprise that develops and commercializes technology and manages laboratories for government customers. Headquartered in Columbus, Ohio, Battelle has a vast science and technology reach. National Laboratories for the Department of Energy - Brookhaven National Laboratory, Oak Ridge National Laboratory, Pacific Northwest National Laboratory, and National Renewable Energy Laboratory, and most recently Idaho National Laboratory. Mr. Inglis joined Battelle in October 2004 after a 32-year career with Ford Motor Company, most recently as Group Vice President-Business Strategy.He played a key role in Ford's global governance and strategy and in championing diversity and talent development processes. During his tenure at Ford, he held several key positions: Chief Financial Officer-Group Vice President, Head-Ford North American and Corporate Vice President, President-Ford South American and Corporate Vice President, Head-Global Product and Business Strategy and Corporate Vice President. In addition, Mr. Inglis held posts in Ford Lio Ho-Taiwan and Ford Europe-Essex, England.Mr. Inglis earned his B.A. in Business Economics (with honors) from Strathclyde University in Glasgow, Scotland.He currently serves on the boards of directors for Brookhaven Science Associates, LLC; UT-Battelle, LLC; and Carpenter Technology Corporation, a leading manufacturer and distributor of specialist alloys and engineered products.He is a member of The Conference Board Council of CFOs.



